Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel!). Pop the wedges on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle with @oil{for roasting}, sprinkle on half of the @Provencal herbs{1/2%pack} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat in the oil, then roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

Trim the @aubergine{1} then halve lengthways. Chop each half into four long strips then chop widthways into roughly 2cm pieces. Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm chunks. Pop the veggies onto another baking tray and drizzle with @oil{for roasting}. Sprinkle on the remaining @Provencal herbs{remaining}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and use your hands to coat the veggies evenly. Roast in your oven until soft and charred, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Peel and grate the @garlic{1/2%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}). Finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{1/2%bunch}(finely chopped) (stalks and all). In a #small bowl{}, mix the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml} and @olive oil{2%tbsp} together. Stir in the flat leaf parsley and as much garlic as you fancy.

> We recommend starting with a tiny amount, tasting and adding more if you want the dressing extra garlicky!

When the veggies have about 10 mins left, put a #frying pan{} on high heat with a drizzle of @oil{for cooking}. Season the @21 Day Aged British Sirloin Steaks{2} with @salt{} and @pepper{}. When the oil is hot, lay the steaks in the pan and brown for ~{1%minute} on each side. Lower the heat slightly and cook for another ~{1-2%minutes} on each side for medium rare.

> Cook for 1-2 mins more if you like it more cooked. The steak is safe to eat when the outside is cooked.

When the steaks are cooked, transfer them to your #chopping board{}, cover with #foil{} and allow to rest for ~{2%minutes}. Pop the @wild rocket{40%g} into a #bowl{} and pour in half of the dressing. When ready, add the roasted veggies to the bowl and toss to coat in the dressing. Get ready to serve.

Share the wedges between your plates and serve the salad alongside. Slice the steak and arrange on the plate. Finish by spooning the remaining dressing over the steak. Tuck in!